  "signal_description": "The query retrieves the total number of cases and the number of cases with changes, along with the invoice payment term. It does this by first selecting the case ID and determining if there were any changes made based on specific event names. If there were changes, the case ID is counted, otherwise it is excluded. The invoice payment term is also selected. This is done by first flattening the 'defaultview-124' table and then selecting the case ID, event name, and the 'Last FI Invoice Item Terms of Payment Key' column as the invoice payment term. The results are then ordered in descending order by the total number of cases and limited to 20 rows."
